      ---
      
      ## Summary
      
      Replace FID-006 v2's read-only 3-card `/manifest` viewer with the actual **soul builder** feature: an interactive authoring flow that mirrors savant-orig's `ControlFrame::SoulManifest` + `ControlFrame::BulkManifest` paths. The form captures `prompt` (textarea) + `name` (text) + `bootstrap_tier` (4-variant select) and dispatches a `manifest_soul` IPC command that returns a templated soul string (mirror of `generate_template_soul`). A second panel captures a `AgentManifestPlan[]` JSON array and dispatches a `bulk_manifest` command (server enforces SEC #8 — 10 agents max). Both commands are stubbed in Phase 1 via the existing `src/lib/mock-ipc.ts` pattern; the result is persisted to `localStorage["LS_SOUL_BUILT"]` for inspection on subsequent visits. The v2 file-resident persona infrastructure (`src/lib/soul.ts`, `src/types/raw.d.ts`, `next.config.mjs` webpack `asset/source` rule, `workspace-savant/` scaffold, `src/app/chat/page.tsx` `SOUL_PROMPT` import) is **kept unchanged** — the chat's `SOUL_PROMPT` remains the build-time canonical persona per LESSON-018. The v2 3-card baseline display is preserved as **Section 4 (Active Baseline)** of the new manifest page, reading from `@/lib/soul` exactly as v2 did.
      
      ---
      
      ## Environment
      
      - **OS:** Windows 11 (savant-orig paths use `C:\Users\spenc\dev\Savant-backup\`)
      - **Language/Runtime:** TypeScript 5.7 (renderer) over Node 22, savant-orig in Rust (informational only)
      - **Tool Versions:** Next.js 15.0, React 19.2, HeroUI v3 alpha, Tauri 2.4 (renderer boundary), @tauri-apps/api 2.x
      - **Commit/State:** main @ `CHANGELOG.md` `[Unreleased]` window; FID-006 v2 archived; v2 file-resident infrastructure (5 `workspace-savant/` files + `src/lib/soul.ts` + `src/types/raw.d.ts` + `next.config.mjs` webpack rule + `src/app/chat/page.tsx` import) is in place and ratified
      
      ---
      
      ## Detailed Description
      
      ### Problem
      
      FID-006 v2 built a **read-only viewer** of an existing `workspace-savant/SOUL.md`. The actual feature in savant-orig is an **interactive authoring flow**:
      
      - `dashboard/src/app/page.tsx:80-87` has a form with name input + prompt textarea + BootstrapTier buttons + a "Generate" button onClick that calls `sendControlFrame("SoulManifest", { prompt, name, bootstrap_tier })`.
      - The Rust gateway receives the `ControlFrame::SoulManifest` frame and calls `generate_template_soul(prompt, name, birth_date)` at `crates/gateway/src/handlers/mod.rs:2031`, which produces an 18-section markdown template (the build-time default for the agent's SOUL.md).
      - The rendered SOUL.md is written to disk by `load_agent` (`registry.rs:192-196` disk loader), and the chat's `Persona (SOUL)` formatted string picks up the new soul.
      
      The v2 viewer had no input box. v3 builds the input box + dispatch + status panel + BulkManifest panel + Active Baseline display.
      
